# App.tsx Round 2 patches

Apply these str_replace patches to your mainline App.tsx. Each is a
small additive change; no existing line is removed except where
required to add the new import / new route.

The patches assume your mainline matches the state confirmed in the
Round 2 kickoff (v2.2 + C1 + C2 Round 1 absorbed):

- /dashboard route exists, wired to Dashboard
- /party/:partyKey wired to PartyDetailPage
- /review and /review/:type wired to ReviewQueuePage
- / wired to upload/preview view

If your mainline differs from this state, apply manually rather than
running the patches blindly.

## Patch 1 - Add import for AgingReportPage

Find this block (existing imports for pages and components):

```typescript
import { ReviewQueuePage } from './components/review/ReviewQueuePage';
```

Add immediately after it:

```typescript
import { AgingReportPage } from './pages/AgingReportPage';
```

If your mainline already imports PartyDetailPage from './components/party/PartyDetailPage'
on the line above, put the new import on a fresh line after that one.
Order does not matter for compilation; cluster page imports together.

## Patch 2 - Add /aging route inside <Routes>

Find your existing Routes block. It should contain (in some order):

```tsx
<Route path="/dashboard" element={...} />
<Route path="/review" element={<ReviewQueuePage result={result} />} />
<Route path="/review/:type" element={<ReviewQueuePage result={result} />} />
<Route path="/party/:partyKey" element={<PartyDetailPage result={result} />} />
<Route path="/" element={...} />
```

Add a new <Route> entry for /aging. Recommended position: after
/party/:partyKey and before /, so all named routes precede the
catch-all root route:

```tsx
<Route
  path="/aging"
  element={(
    <AgingReportPage
      result={result}
      onBackToDashboard={() => navigate('/dashboard')}
    />
  )}
/>
```

## Patch 3 - Add onOpenAging prop to Dashboard usage

Find your existing Dashboard route inside <Routes>:

```tsx
<Route
  path="/dashboard"
  element={(
    <Dashboard
      lang={lang}
      result={result}
      onBackToUpload={() => navigate('/')}
      onOpenReview={...}
      onOpenReviewCategory={openReviewRoute}
      onOpenParty={(partyKey) => navigate(`/party/${partyKey}`)}
      detailsNotice={detailsNotice}
    />
  )}
/>
```

Add an onOpenAging prop pointing to /aging. Place it on its own line
in the props list, near onOpenParty:

```tsx
onOpenAging={() => navigate('/aging')}
```

The resulting Dashboard element should include all existing props
plus onOpenAging.

## Verification

After applying these three patches:

1. `npm.cmd run build` should succeed.
2. The dev server should serve /aging as the AgingReportPage component.
3. The dashboard should show an "Open Collection Workbench" button
   (added by Dashboard.tsx patches in dashboard-tsx.patch).
4. Round 2 invariants should pass (`node --experimental-strip-types
   .\tools\test-aging-report-ui.mjs`).
